      "writtenOn": "2016-07-25T12:16:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I find that this makes the code more difficult to understand, and the implementation is also probably much worse:\n\n  auto it \u003d std::find_if(mGuests.begin(), mGuests.end(),\n                                   [guest](const std::unique\u003cAdbGuestAgent\u003e\u0026 p) {\n                                       return p.get() \u003d\u003d guest;\n                                   });\n  if (it !\u003d mGuests.end()) {\n      mGuests.erase();\n  }\n\nAn alternative is to use std::remove_if:\n\n  std::remove_if(mGuests.begin(), mGuests.end(),\n      [guest](const std::unique_ptr\u003cAdbGuestAgent\u003e\u0026 p) {\n          return p.get() \u003d\u003d guest;\n      });\n\nWhich isn\u0027t too sexy either.",
