        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-25T12:16:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, I think this is here because it was part of the code you contributed lately (of which this is a refactor), I just kept it here without thinking too much about it. Thanks for pointing this out.\n\nI agree we don\u0027t need to do that on onHostServerConnection, however, it\u0027s important to do that when there is no active connection and a new guest arrives. The ADB host server might have been killed, restarted, but didn\u0027t find the emulator because it wasn\u0027t using one of the 16 auto-scanned port values.\n\nI\u0027m not sure what your last paragraph means. When this method is called, stopListener() will already have been called by the caller on the AsyncSocketServer.",
      "parentUuid": "8a91eb63_d15ab2f8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 99,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 101,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
