    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8a91eb63_918f4ad1",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbHostListener.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-21T19:43:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Combined with my suggestion of returning an opaque handle from |addGuest|, you can make this a std::list and return (typedef\u0027ed) the iterator from inserting the guest.\n\n|addGuest| is not a throughput critical insert so vector --\u003e list is OK.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4a88d372_515d347f",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbHostListener.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-25T12:16:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this would add un-necessary complexity to the code without clarity benefits anyway (see other comment).",
      "parentUuid": "8a91eb63_918f4ad1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
