    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ca2e8326_55518c0a",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbTypes.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 54,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-25T12:16:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it\u0027s quite important with regards to lifecycle management.",
      "parentUuid": "8a91eb63_6636a6ee",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 53,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 54,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8a91eb63_262d7e99",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbTypes.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-21T18:58:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This API implies that the user keeps a pointer to the AdbGuestAgent even after calling |addGuest| whereby it transferred ownership of the AdbGuestAgent to us.\n\nI\u0027d recommend that addGuest returns an opaque id that the user can use with deleteGuest.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0a8edb80_8f729515",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbTypes.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-25T07:21:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I strongly second it. Having a pointer to something that\u0027s owned by another object is a common path to use after free bugs. Either opaque id or shared_ptr/weak_ptr pair would be a better mach here IMO",
      "parentUuid": "8a91eb63_262d7e99",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8a248b48_737620e9",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbTypes.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-25T12:16:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I\u0027ll try to see if there is a better interface for this then.",
      "parentUuid": "0a8edb80_8f729515",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ea76e749_0e10eba4",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbTypes.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-25T12:16:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure I understand what you mean by \"user\". This is called from one of |pipe|\u0027s methods (onGuestClose()), so of course it will retain a pointer to it. An opaque pointer will hide the fact but will not make any of the implementation simpler to understand/maintain.",
      "parentUuid": "8a91eb63_262d7e99",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 48
      },
